  "texts": [
    "New technologies have become game-changers in advancing content-based customer recommendation systems, risk analysis systems for banks, as well as applications for stock markets (Sert et al., 2020).",
    "Social media platforms have served as ideal sources for big data, feeding prediction systems (Candi et al., 2018; Stylos and Zwiegelaar, 2019; Pekar, 2020; Stylos et al., 2021).",
    "For example, information about cryptocurrencies is spread through various social media outlets and given the benefits of big data, a growing body of the literature is examining the use of text-and news-based measures as sources of information for forecasting and assessing economic events (Park et al., 2021).",
    "From a slightly different perspective, news texts were converted into feature vectors with word representations (Gunduz, 2021).",
    "Stock market forecasting models to improve prediction performance by employing unsupervised learning models to analyse investor sentiments with respect to stock prices can take place where explicit labels are not specified when training the network (Baldi, 2012)."
